   <strow>
    <stentry>1. <xref href="CFR_step_1.dita#concept_s2k_b35_st" id="quickStartHPcloudStep1_"
              ><keyword keyref="quickStartHPcloudStep1"/></xref><p>2. <b><keyword
                keyref="quickStartHPcloudStep2" id="quickStartHPcloudStep2"/></b></p><p>3. <xref
              conref="CFR_step_1.dita#concept_s2k_b35_st/quickStartHPcloudStep3_"/></p><p>4. <xref
              conref="CFR_step_1.dita#concept_s2k_b35_st/quickStartHPcloudStep4_"/></p><p>5. <xref
              conref="CFR_step_1.dita#concept_s2k_b35_st/quickStartHPcloudStep5_"/></p>6. <xref
            conref="CFR_step_1.dita#concept_s2k_b35_st/quickStartHPcloudStep6_"/></stentry>
    <stentry><b>Downloading <keyword keyref="prodLong"/></b><p>You can use <keyword
              keyref="prodShort"/> to push Docker images and application code to the server, to
            start and stop applications, to link <keyword keyref="opnStckShort"/> services to
            applications, and to perform other application management operations. <keyword
              keyref="prodShort"/> works on Linux, Mac OS X, and Windows.</p><ul id="ul_cfn_rm1_tt">
            <li><xref
                href="https://a248.e.akamai.net/cdn.hpcloudsvc.com/gb0e6744f83898b90eb8ff0a2e16a9529/prodae1/hcf-1.0.0.102_master/hcf-1.0.0.102_master.tar.gz"
                format="html" scope="external">Download <keyword keyref="prodShort"/>
                <keyword keyref="prodVerLong"/></xref>
            </li>
          </ul><note type="tip">To decompress <filepath>tar.gz</filepath> files on Windows, you can
            use a file archiver such as <xref href="http://www.7-zip.org/" format="html"
              scope="external">7zip</xref>.</note><b>Downloading and Installing the Cloud Foundy
            Command-Line Interface (CLI)</b><p>You can use the Cloud Foundry CLI to deploy and
            manage your applications. Click the download link appropriate for your operating
            system:</p><ul id="ul_bp4_fpb_tt">
            <li>Debian <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=debian32&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=debian64&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
            <li>RedHat <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=redhat32&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=redhat64&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
            <li>Mac OS X <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=macosx64&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
            <li>Windows <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=windows32&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=windows64&amp;version=6.13.0&amp;source=github-rel"
                format="html" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
          </ul><note>Ensure that you add the Cloud Foundry CLI to your <codeph>PATH</codeph>
            environment variable.</note><b>Downloading and Installing the Terraform CLI</b><p>You
            can use the Terraform 0.6.3 CLI and higher to construct, manage, update, or delete
              <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> clusters. Click the download link appropriate for your
            operating system:</p><ul id="ul_d1k_5k1_tt">
            <li>Linux <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_linux_386.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_linux_amd64.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x64</xref> | <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_linux_arm.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">Arm</xref></li>
            <li>Mac OS X <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_darwin_386.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_darwin_amd64.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
            <li>Windows <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_windows_386.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x86</xref> | <xref
                href="https://dl.bintray.com/mitchellh/terraform/terraform_0.6.4_windows_amd64.zip"
                format="zip" scope="external">x64</xref></li>
          </ul><note>Ensure that you add Terraform to your <codeph>PATH</codeph> environment
            variable. To set the variable on Linux and Mac OS X, <xref
              href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14637979/how-to-permanently-set-path-on-linux"
              format="html" scope="external">see this page</xref>. To set it on Windows, <xref
              href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1618280/where-can-i-set-path-to-make-exe-on-windows"
              format="html" scope="external">see this page</xref>. For detailed installation
            instructions, see the <xref
              href="https://terraform.io/intro/getting-started/install.html" format="html"
              scope="external">Terraform installation guide</xref>.</note><xref
            href="CFR_step_3.dita#concept_kpg_fhz_st">
            <image href="../../media/NextButton.png" id="image_gqc_sgp_js" placement="break"/>
          </xref></stentry>
